      <!-- Slide 2: Overview -->
      <div class="slide" id="slide2">
        <div class="slide-indicator">
          2 / 12
          <button class="lang-toggle" onclick="toggleLanguage()">
            <i class="fas fa-language"></i> ID
          </button>
          <button class="theme-toggle" onclick="toggleTheme()">
            <i class="fas fa-moon"></i>
          </button>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-header">
          <div class="en-content">
            <h2 class="slide-title editable" contenteditable="false">
              Overview
            </h2>
          </div>
          <div class="id-content">
            <h2 class="slide-title editable" contenteditable="false">
              Latar Belakang
            </h2>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-content">
          <div class="bilingual">
            <div class="column en-content">
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">Introduction</h3>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Microwave radio links are point-to-point communication systems
                that use high-frequency radio waves (typically 6–80 GHz) to
                transmit large amounts of data between two fixed sites. They
                serve as critical components in telecommunications
                infrastructure, especially in areas where fiber optic deployment
                is impractical or cost-prohibitive.
              </p>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Modern microwave systems offer capacities from several hundred
                Mbps to multiple Gbps, with reliability exceeding 99.999%. They
                are widely used for mobile backhaul, enterprise connectivity,
                and critical infrastructure links.
              </p>
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">Key Principles</h3>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Microwave transmission relies on Line-of-Sight (LOS)
                propagation, requiring clear paths between antennas. The
                technology operates on the principle that radio waves travel in
                straight lines and can be affected by atmospheric conditions,
                terrain, and obstacles.
              </p>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Key technical parameters include frequency bands, modulation
                schemes, channel bandwidth, and transmit power. Modern systems
                use advanced modulation (up to 4096-QAM) and adaptive coding to
                maximize spectral efficiency.
              </p>
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">Applications</h3>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Mobile Backhaul:</strong> Connecting cell sites to
                  core networks
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Enterprise Networks:</strong> High-speed connectivity
                  between campuses
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Last-Mile Access:</strong> Providing broadband
                  services in remote areas
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Backup Links:</strong> Redundant connections for
                  critical infrastructure
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Temporary Deployments:</strong> Rapid deployment for
                  events or disaster recovery
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="column id-content">
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">Pendahuluan</h3>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Radio microwave link adalah sistem komunikasi point-to-point
                yang menggunakan gelombang radio berfrekuensi tinggi (biasanya
                6–80 GHz) untuk mentransmisikan data dalam jumlah besar antara
                dua lokasi tetap. Mereka berfungsi sebagai komponen kritis dalam
                infrastruktur telekomunikasi, terutama di area di mana
                pemasangan serat optik tidak praktis atau terlalu mahal.
              </p>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Sistem microwave modern menawarkan kapasitas dari beberapa ratus
                Mbps hingga beberapa Gbps, dengan keandalan melebihi 99,999%.
                Mereka banyak digunakan untuk backhaul seluler, konektivitas
                enterprise, dan link infrastruktur kritis.
              </p>
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">Prinsip Utama</h3>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Transmisi microwave bergantung pada propagasi Line-of-Sight
                (LOS), yang memerlukan jalur yang jelas antara antena. Teknologi
                ini beroperasi pada prinsip bahwa gelombang radio merambat dalam
                garis lurus dan dapat dipengaruhi oleh kondisi atmosfer, medan,
                dan rintangan.
              </p>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Parameter teknis utama meliputi pita frekuensi, skema modulasi,
                bandwidth kanal, dan daya transmisi. Sistem modern menggunakan
                modulasi canggih (hingga 4096-QAM) dan pengkodean adaptif untuk
                memaksimalkan efisiensi spektral.
              </p>
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">Aplikasi</h3>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Backhaul Seluler:</strong> Menghubungkan situs seluler
                  ke jaringan inti
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Jaringan Enterprise:</strong> Konektivitas kecepatan
                  tinggi antar kampus
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Akses Last-Mile:</strong> Menyediakan layanan
                  broadband di area terpencil
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Link Cadangan:</strong> Koneksi redundan untuk
                  infrastruktur kritis
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Penyebaran Sementara:</strong> Penyebaran cepat untuk
                  acara atau pemulihan bencana
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-footer editable" contenteditable="false">
          Prepared by: Imam Wahyudi – Senior Microwave Technical Support
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Slide 3: Performance Parameters -->
      <div class="slide" id="slide3">
        <div class="slide-indicator">
          3 / 12
          <button class="lang-toggle" onclick="toggleLanguage()">
            <i class="fas fa-language"></i> ID
          </button>
          <button class="theme-toggle" onclick="toggleTheme()">
            <i class="fas fa-moon"></i>
          </button>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-header">
          <div class="en-content">
            <h2 class="slide-title editable" contenteditable="false">
              Performance Parameters
            </h2>
          </div>
          <div class="id-content">
            <h2 class="slide-title editable" contenteditable="false">
              Parameter Performa
            </h2>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-content">
          <div class="bilingual">
            <div class="column en-content">
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Key Performance Indicators
              </h3>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Monitoring microwave link performance requires tracking several
                critical parameters to ensure optimal operation and service
                quality. These indicators help engineers identify potential
                issues before they impact service availability.
              </p>
              <table class="param-table">
                <thead>
                  <tr>
                    <th>Parameter</th>
                    <th>Description & Threshold</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr>
                    <td>RSL</td>
                    <td>
                      Received Signal Level - indicates link strength. Normal
                      range: -30 to -70 dBm
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>BER</td>
                    <td>
                      Bit Error Rate - measures transmission quality. Good:
                      &lt;10⁻⁶, Acceptable: &lt;10⁻³
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>ES/SES</td>
                    <td>
                      Error Seconds / Severely Errored Seconds - measures error
                      duration
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>UAS</td>
                    <td>
                      Unavailable Seconds - measures downtime. Target: &lt;28.8
                      seconds/month
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>Throughput</td>
                    <td>Actual data rate achieved vs. configured capacity</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>Availability</td>
                    <td>Percentage of uptime. Standard: 99.999% (5 nines)</td>
                  </tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Performance Standards
              </h3>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                ITU-T G.828 defines stringent requirements for international
                connections, while ITU-T G.826 provides error performance
                objectives. Carrier-grade networks typically require 99.999%
                availability with latency &lt;5ms for critical applications.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="column id-content">
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Indikator Kinerja Utama
              </h3>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Memantau performa link microwave memerlukan pelacakan beberapa
                parameter kritis untuk memastikan operasi optimal dan kualitas
                layanan. Indikator ini membantu engineer mengidentifikasi
                masalah potensial sebelum memengaruhi ketersediaan layanan.
              </p>
              <table class="param-table">
                <thead>
                  <tr>
                    <th>Parameter</th>
                    <th>Deskripsi & Ambang Batas</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr>
                    <td>RSL</td>
                    <td>
                      Level Sinyal Terima - menunjukkan kekuatan link. Rentang
                      normal: -30 hingga -70 dBm
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>BER</td>
                    <td>
                      Rasio Kesalahan Bit - mengukur kualitas transmisi. Baik:
                      &lt;10⁻⁶, Dapat diterima: &lt;10⁻³
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>ES/SES</td>
                    <td>
                      Detik Kesalahan / Detik Kesalahan Berat - mengukur durasi
                      kesalahan
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>UAS</td>
                    <td>
                      Detik Tidak Tersedia - mengukur downtime. Target: &lt;28.8
                      detik/bulan
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>Throughput</td>
                    <td>
                      Laju data aktual yang dicapai vs kapasitas yang
                      dikonfigurasi
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>Availability</td>
                    <td>
                      Persentase waktu aktif. Standar: 99.999% (5 sembilan)
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">Standar Performa</h3>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                ITU-T G.828 mendefinisikan persyaratan ketat untuk koneksi
                internasional, sementara ITU-T G.826 menyediakan tujuan performa
                kesalahan. Jaringan kelas carrier biasanya memerlukan
                ketersediaan 99,999% dengan latensi &lt;5ms untuk aplikasi
                kritis.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-footer editable" contenteditable="false">
          Prepared by: Imam Wahyudi – Senior Microwave Technical Support
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Slide 4: Link Budget Analysis
      <div class="slide" id="slide4">
        <div class="slide-indicator">
          4 / 13
          <button class="lang-toggle" onclick="toggleLanguage()">
            <i class="fas fa-language"></i> ID
          </button>
          <button class="theme-toggle" onclick="toggleTheme()">
            <i class="fas fa-moon"></i>
          </button>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-header">
          <div class="en-content">
            <h2 class="slide-title editable" contenteditable="false">
              Link Budget Analysis
            </h2>
          </div>
          <div class="id-content">
            <h2 class="slide-title editable" contenteditable="false">
              Analisis Link Budget
            </h2>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-content">
          <div class="bilingual">
            <div class="column en-content">
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Link Budget Fundamentals
              </h3>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Link budget analysis is crucial for designing reliable microwave
                links. It calculates the expected received signal level and
                ensures adequate fade margin for various atmospheric conditions.
              </p>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <strong>Basic Equation:</strong><br />
                Pr = Pt + Gt + Gr - (FSPL + Lloss)
              </p>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Where:<br />
                Pr = Received Power (dBm)<br />
                Pt = Transmitted Power (dBm)<br />
                Gt/Gr = Antenna Gains (dBi)<br />
                FSPL = Free Space Path Loss (dB)<br />
                Lloss = System Losses (dB)
              </p>
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Path Loss Calculation
              </h3>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Free Space Path Loss (FSPL) is calculated as:<br />
                FSPL = 92.4 + 20log10(f) + 20log10(d)<br />
                Where f = frequency in GHz, d = distance in km
              </p>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                For example, a 15 GHz link over 20 km:<br />
                FSPL = 92.4 + 20log10(15) + 20log10(20) = 142.4 dB
              </p>
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">Fade Margin</h3>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Fade margin is the additional signal strength above the receiver
                threshold to account for atmospheric conditions. Typical
                requirements:
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Short links (&lt;10 km): 15-20 dB
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Medium links (10-30 km): 20-30 dB
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Long links (&gt;30 km): 30-40 dB
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="column id-content">
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Dasar Link Budget
              </h3>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Analisis link budget sangat penting untuk merancang link
                microwave yang andal. Ini menghitung level sinyal terima yang
                diharapkan dan memastikan fade margin yang memadai untuk
                berbagai kondisi atmosfer.
              </p>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <strong>Persamaan Dasar:</strong><br />
                Pr = Pt + Gt + Gr - (FSPL + Lloss)
              </p>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Dimana:<br />
                Pr = Daya Terima (dBm)<br />
                Pt = Daya Transmisi (dBm)<br />
                Gt/Gr = Gain Antena (dBi)<br />
                FSPL = Path Loss Ruang Bebas (dB)<br />
                Lloss = Losses Sistem (dB)
              </p>
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Perhitungan Path Loss
              </h3>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Free Space Path Loss (FSPL) dihitung sebagai:<br />
                FSPL = 92.4 + 20log10(f) + 20log10(d)<br />
                Dimana f = frekuensi dalam GHz, d = jarak dalam km
              </p>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Sebagai contoh, link 15 GHz sejauh 20 km:<br />
                FSPL = 92.4 + 20log10(15) + 20log10(20) = 142.4 dB
              </p>
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">Fade Margin</h3>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Fade margin adalah kekuatan sinyal tambahan di atas ambang
                penerima untuk memperhitungkan kondisi atmosfer. Persyaratan
                tipikal:
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Link pendek (&lt;10 km): 15-20 dB
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Link sedang (10-30 km): 20-30 dB
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Link panjang (&gt;30 km): 30-40 dB
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-footer editable" contenteditable="false">
          Prepared by: Imam Wahyudi – Senior Microwave Technical Support
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Slide 5: System Components -->
      <div class="slide" id="slide5">
        <div class="slide-indicator">
          4 / 12
          <button class="lang-toggle" onclick="toggleLanguage()">
            <i class="fas fa-language"></i> ID
          </button>
          <button class="theme-toggle" onclick="toggleTheme()">
            <i class="fas fa-moon"></i>
          </button>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-header">
          <div class="en-content">
            <h2 class="slide-title editable" contenteditable="false">
              System Components
            </h2>
          </div>
          <div class="id-content">
            <h2 class="slide-title editable" contenteditable="false">
              Komponen Sistem
            </h2>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-content">
          <div class="bilingual">
            <div class="column en-content">
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">Main Components</h3>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                A complete microwave radio link system consists of several key
                components working together to provide reliable wireless
                communication. Understanding each component's function is
                essential for proper installation and maintenance.
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong
                    ><i class="fas fa-satellite-dish"></i> ODU (Outdoor
                    Unit)</strong
                  >
                  – The radio transceiver mounted near the antenna. It handles
                  RF signal conversion, amplification, and filtering. Modern
                  ODUs are fully outdoor-rated with IP67 protection and operate
                  in extreme temperatures (-40°C to +65°C).
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong
                    ><i class="fas fa-server"></i> IDU (Indoor Unit)</strong
                  >
                  – The modem and interface equipment typically installed in a
                  shelter or equipment room. It provides network interfaces
                  (Ethernet, STM-1, etc.), performs multiplexing/demultiplexing,
                  and manages the ODU remotely.
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong
                    ><i class="fas fa-broadcast-tower"></i> Antenna</strong
                  >
                  – Parabolic reflector that focuses RF energy. Sizes range from
                  0.3m to 4.2m depending on frequency and distance requirements.
                  Larger antennas provide higher gain and better interference
                  rejection.
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong
                    ><i class="fas fa-network-wired"></i> Transmission
                    Line</strong
                  >
                  – Connects ODU to IDU. Can be coaxial cable for shorter
                  distances or fiber optic for longer distances. Fiber
                  connections eliminate lightning risk and support longer
                  distances.
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong
                    ><i class="fas fa-desktop"></i> Management System
                    (NMS)</strong
                  >
                  – Software platform for monitoring, configuration, and fault
                  management. Provides real-time performance metrics, alarm
                  management, and remote troubleshooting capabilities.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="column id-content">
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">Komponen Utama</h3>
              <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Sistem radio microwave link lengkap terdiri dari beberapa
                komponen kunci yang bekerja sama untuk menyediakan komunikasi
                nirkabel yang andal. Memahami fungsi setiap komponen sangat
                penting untuk instalasi dan pemeliharaan yang tepat.
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong
                    ><i class="fas fa-satellite-dish"></i> ODU (Outdoor
                    Unit)</strong
                  >
                  – Pemancar/penerima radio yang dipasang dekat antena. Ini
                  menangani konversi sinyal RF, amplifikasi, dan filtering. ODU
                  modern sepenuhnya tahan luar ruangan dengan perlindungan IP67
                  dan beroperasi dalam suhu ekstrem (-40°C hingga +65°C).
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong
                    ><i class="fas fa-server"></i> IDU (Indoor Unit)</strong
                  >
                  – Peralatan modem dan antarmuka yang biasanya dipasang di
                  shelter atau ruang peralatan. Ini menyediakan antarmuka
                  jaringan (Ethernet, STM-1, dll.), melakukan
                  multiplexing/demultiplexing, dan mengelola ODU dari jarak
                  jauh.
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong><i class="fas fa-broadcast-tower"></i> Antena</strong>
                  – Reflektor parabola yang memfokuskan energi RF. Ukuran
                  berkisar dari 0.3m hingga 4.2m tergantung pada persyaratan
                  frekuensi dan jarak. Antena yang lebih besar memberikan gain
                  lebih tinggi dan penolakan interferensi yang lebih baik.
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong
                    ><i class="fas fa-network-wired"></i> Jalur
                    Transmisi</strong
                  >
                  – Menghubungkan ODU ke IDU. Dapat berupa kabel koaksial untuk
                  jarak yang lebih pendek atau serat optik untuk jarak yang
                  lebih panjang. Koneksi serat menghilangkan risiko petir dan
                  mendukung jarak yang lebih panjang.
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong
                    ><i class="fas fa-desktop"></i> Sistem Manajemen
                    (NMS)</strong
                  >
                  – Platform perangkat lunak untuk pemantauan, konfigurasi, dan
                  manajemen fault. Menyediakan metrik performa real-time,
                  manajemen alarm, dan kemampuan pemecahan masalah dari jarak
                  jauh.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-footer editable" contenteditable="false">
          Prepared by: Imam Wahyudi – Senior Microwave Technical Support
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Slide 6: Technical Case 1 -->
      <div class="slide" id="slide6">
        <div class="slide-indicator">
          5 / 12
          <button class="lang-toggle" onclick="toggleLanguage()">
            <i class="fas fa-language"></i> ID
          </button>
          <button class="theme-toggle" onclick="toggleTheme()">
            <i class="fas fa-moon"></i>
          </button>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-header">
          <div class="en-content">
            <h2 class="slide-title editable" contenteditable="false">
              Technical Case 1: Degraded RSL Level
            </h2>
          </div>
          <div class="id-content">
            <h2 class="slide-title editable" contenteditable="false">
              Kasus Teknis 1: Penurunan Level RSL
            </h2>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-content">
          <div class="case-description">
            <div class="bilingual">
              <div class="column en-content">
                <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Case Description
                </h3>
                <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Incident:</strong> A sudden degradation of the
                  Received Signal Level (RSL) was observed on a critical 23 GHz
                  microwave hop connecting a major cell site to the core
                  network. The RSL dropped from –42 dBm to –68 dBm over a
                  24-hour period, causing increased BER and reduced throughput.
                </p>
                <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Impact:</strong> The degradation affected 4G/LTE
                  services for approximately 50,000 subscribers, with increased
                  latency and packet loss. While the link remained operational,
                  service quality was significantly impacted.
                </p>
                <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Initial Assessment:</strong> NMS alarms indicated "RSL
                  Degradation" and "Increased BER" but no hardware faults were
                  reported. Weather conditions were normal with no significant
                  rain events.
                </p>
                <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Root Cause Analysis
                </h3>
                <ul>
                  <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                    <i class="fas fa-arrows-alt"></i>
                    <strong>Antenna Misalignment</strong> – Visual inspection
                    revealed slight movement of the antenna due to strong winds
                    (up to 80 km/h recorded in the area). The mounting bolts had
                    loosened over time, allowing the antenna to shift by
                    approximately 2 degrees.
                  </li>
                  <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                    <i class="fas fa-rust"></i>
                    <strong>Connector Corrosion</strong> – Moisture ingress in
                    the RF connectors caused oxidation, increasing insertion
                    loss by approximately 3 dB. This was confirmed with VSWR
                    measurements showing 1.8:1 (normal: &lt;1.5:1).
                  </li>
                  <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                    <i class="fas fa-mountain"></i>
                    <strong>Vegetation Growth</strong> – New foliage on a tree
                    line partially obstructed the Fresnel zone, causing
                    additional diffraction loss estimated at 2-3 dB.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="column id-content">
                <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Deskripsi Kasus
                </h3>
                <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Insiden:</strong> Penurunan mendadak pada level daya
                  terima (RSL) diamati pada hop microwave 23 GHz kritis yang
                  menghubungkan situs seluler utama ke jaringan inti. RSL turun
                  dari –42 dBm menjadi –68 dBm selama periode 24 jam,
                  menyebabkan peningkatan BER dan penurunan throughput.
                </p>
                <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Dampak:</strong> Degradasi memengaruhi layanan 4G/LTE
                  untuk sekitar 50.000 pelanggan, dengan peningkatan latensi dan
                  packet loss. Meskipun link tetap operasional, kualitas layanan
                  sangat terpengaruh.
                </p>
                <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Assesmen Awal:</strong> Alarm NMS menunjukkan
                  "Degradasi RSL" dan "BER Meningkat" tetapi tidak ada fault
                  perangkat keras yang dilaporkan. Kondisi cuaca normal tanpa
                  peristiwa hujan signifikan.
                </p>
                <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Analisis Akar Masalah
                </h3>
                <ul>
                  <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                    <i class="fas fa-arrows-alt"></i>
                    <strong>Perubahan Arah Antena</strong> – Inspeksi visual
                    mengungkapkan pergerakan sedikit antena karena angin kencang
                    (hingga 80 km/h tercatat di area). Baut pemasangan telah
                    longgar seiring waktu, memungkinkan antena bergeser sekitar
                    2 derajat.
                  </li>
                  <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                    <i class="fas fa-rust"></i>
                    <strong>Korosi Konektor</strong> – Masuknya kelembapan dalam
                    konektor RF menyebabkan oksidasi, meningkatkan insertion
                    loss sekitar 3 dB. Ini dikonfirmasi dengan pengukuran VSWR
                    menunjukkan 1.8:1 (normal: &lt;1.5:1).
                  </li>
                  <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                    <i class="fas fa-mountain"></i>
                    <strong>Pertumbuhan Vegetasi</strong> – Dedaunan baru pada
                    garis pohon sebagian menghalangi Fresnel zone, menyebabkan
                    diffraction loss tambahan diperkirakan 2-3 dB.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-footer editable" contenteditable="false">
          Prepared by: Imam Wahyudi – Senior Microwave Technical Support
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Slide 7: Solution 1 -->
      <div class="slide" id="slide7">
        <div class="slide-indicator">
          6 / 12
          <button class="lang-toggle" onclick="toggleLanguage()">
            <i class="fas fa-language"></i> ID
          </button>
          <button class="theme-toggle" onclick="toggleTheme()">
            <i class="fas fa-moon"></i>
          </button>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-header">
          <div class="en-content">
            <h2 class="slide-title editable" contenteditable="false">
              Technical Solution 1: Degraded RSL
            </h2>
          </div>
          <div class="id-content">
            <h2 class="slide-title editable" contenteditable="false">
              Solusi Teknis 1: Penurunan RSL
            </h2>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-content">
          <div class="solution-steps">
            <div class="step en-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-search"></i> Site Assessment
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Conducted comprehensive site survey including physical
                  inspection of antenna mounting structure, connectors, and
                  transmission lines
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Used spectrum analyzer to identify any external interference
                  sources
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Performed path profile analysis to confirm Fresnel zone
                  clearance
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="step en-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-tools"></i> Corrective Actions
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Antenna Realignment:</strong> Secured mounting bolts
                  and performed fine-tuning alignment using spectrum analyzer.
                  Achieved RSL improvement of 18 dB
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Connector Maintenance:</strong> Replaced corroded RF
                  connectors and applied weatherproofing compound. Measured VSWR
                  improved to 1.3:1
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Vegetation Management:</strong> Coordinated with local
                  authorities to trim vegetation obstructing the path
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="step en-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i> Performance Validation
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Monitored link performance for 72 hours after corrective
                  actions
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  RSL stabilized at -40 dBm with normal fluctuations of ±2 dB
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  BER returned to normal levels (&lt;10⁻⁸) with no error seconds
                  recorded
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Throughput restored to full capacity (1 Gbps)
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="step en-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> Preventive Measures
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Implemented quarterly inspection schedule for all critical
                  microwave sites
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Installed torque indicators on antenna mounting bolts for easy
                  monitoring
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Enhanced weatherproofing of all external connectors with
                  heat-shrink tubing
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Established vegetation management agreement with property
                  owners
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="step id-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-search"></i> Assesmen Situs
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Melakukan survei situs komprehensif termasuk inspeksi fisik
                  struktur pemasangan antena, konektor, dan jalur transmisi
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Menggunakan spectrum analyzer untuk mengidentifikasi sumber
                  interferensi eksternal
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Melakukan analisis path profile untuk mengkonfirmasi clearance
                  Fresnel zone
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="step id-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-tools"></i> Tindakan Korektif
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Realignment Antena:</strong> Mengamankan baut
                  pemasangan dan melakukan penyetelan halus menggunakan spectrum
                  analyzer. Mencapai peningkatan RSL 18 dB
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Pemeliharaan Konektor:</strong> Mengganti konektor RF
                  yang berkarat dan menerapkan senyawa waterproofing. VSWR
                  terukur meningkat menjadi 1.3:1
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Manajemen Vegetasi:</strong> Berkoordinasi dengan
                  otoritas setempat untuk memangkas vegetasi yang menghalangi
                  jalur
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="step id-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i> Validasi Performa
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Memantau performa link selama 72 jam setelah tindakan korektif
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  RSL stabil pada -40 dBm dengan fluktuasi normal ±2 dB
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  BER kembali ke level normal (&lt;10⁻⁸) tanpa detik kesalahan
                  tercatat
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Throughput dipulihkan ke kapasitas penuh (1 Gbps)
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="step id-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> Tindakan Preventif
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Mengimplementasikan jadwal inspeksi triwulan untuk semua situs
                  microwave kritis
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Memasang indikator torsi pada baut pemasangan antena untuk
                  pemantauan mudah
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Meningkatkan waterproofing semua konektor eksternal dengan
                  tabung heat-shrink
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Membuat perjanjian manajemen vegetasi dengan pemilik properti
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-footer editable" contenteditable="false">
          Prepared by: Imam Wahyudi – Senior Microwave Technical Support
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Slide 8: Technical Case 2 -->
      <div class="slide" id="slide8">
        <div class="slide-indicator">
          7 / 12
          <button class="lang-toggle" onclick="toggleLanguage()">
            <i class="fas fa-language"></i> ID
          </button>
          <button class="theme-toggle" onclick="toggleTheme()">
            <i class="fas fa-moon"></i>
          </button>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-header">
          <div class="en-content">
            <h2 class="slide-title editable" contenteditable="false">
              Technical Case 2: Complete Link Failure
            </h2>
          </div>
          <div class="id-content">
            <h2 class="slide-title editable" contenteditable="false">
              Kasus Teknis 2: Kegagalan Link Total
            </h2>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-content">
          <div class="case-description">
            <div class="bilingual">
              <div class="column en-content">
                <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Case Description
                </h3>
                <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Incident:</strong> A complete outage occurred on a 38
                  GHz backbone link connecting two data centers. The NMS showed
                  "Link Down" alarms with no response from either end. The link
                  had been operational for 3 years without prior issues.
                </p>
                <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Impact:</strong> Critical data replication services
                  between data centers were interrupted, affecting business
                  continuity. Backup systems were activated but with reduced
                  capacity.
                </p>
                <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Initial Findings:</strong> Remote access to both sites
                  was unavailable. Weather conditions showed severe thunderstorm
                  activity in the area around the time of failure.
                </p>
                <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Root Cause Analysis
                </h3>
                <ul>
                  <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                    <i class="fas fa-bolt"></i>
                    <strong>Lightning Strike</strong> – Evidence of lightning
                    damage was found at both ends of the link. Surge protectors
                    had activated but were insufficient to protect against a
                    direct strike.
                  </li>
                  <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                    <i class="fas fa-microchip"></i>
                    <strong>ODU Failure</strong> – Both ODUs showed no LED
                    indicators and failed to respond to local craft terminal
                    access. Internal inspection revealed damaged power supply
                    components and RF transceiver sections.
                  </li>
                  <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                    <i class="fas fa-ethernet"></i>
                    <strong>Network Equipment Damage</strong> – Ethernet
                    switches connected to the IDUs also showed damage,
                    indicating the surge propagated through the data lines.
                  </li>
                  <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                    <i class="fas fa-plug"></i>
                    <strong>Power Supply Issues</strong> – Site power systems
                    showed voltage fluctuations during the storm, potentially
                    contributing to equipment vulnerability.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="column id-content">
                <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Deskripsi Kasus
                </h3>
                <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Insiden:</strong> Outage total terjadi pada link
                  backbone 38 GHz yang menghubungkan dua pusat data. NMS
                  menunjukkan alarm "Link Down" tanpa respons dari kedua ujung.
                  Link telah operasional selama 3 tahun tanpa masalah
                  sebelumnya.
                </p>
                <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Dampak:</strong> Layanan replikasi data kritis antara
                  pusat data terganggu, memengaruhi kelangsungan bisnis. Sistem
                  cadangan diaktifkan tetapi dengan kapasitas berkurang.
                </p>
                <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Temuan Awal:</strong> Akses jarak jauh ke kedua situs
                  tidak tersedia. Kondisi cuaca menunjukkan aktivitas badai
                  petir hebat di area sekitar waktu kegagalan.
                </p>
                <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Analisis Akar Masalah
                </h3>
                <ul>
                  <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                    <i class="fas fa-bolt"></i>
                    <strong>Sambaran Petir</strong> – Bukti kerusakan petir
                    ditemukan di kedua ujung link. Arrester telah diaktifkan
                    tetapi tidak cukup untuk melindungi dari sambaran langsung.
                  </li>
                  <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                    <i class="fas fa-microchip"></i>
                    <strong>Kegagalan ODU</strong> – Kedua ODU tidak menunjukkan
                    indikator LED dan gagal merespons akses terminal craft
                    lokal. Inspeksi internal mengungkapkan komponen catu daya
                    dan bagian transceiver RF yang rusak.
                  </li>
                  <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                    <i class="fas fa-ethernet"></i>
                    <strong>Kerusakan Peralatan Jaringan</strong> – Switch
                    Ethernet yang terhubung ke IDU juga menunjukkan kerusakan,
                    menunjukkan surge merambat melalui jalur data.
                  </li>
                  <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                    <i class="fas fa-plug"></i>
                    <strong>Masalah Catu Daya</strong> – Sistem daya situs
                    menunjukkan fluktuasi tegangan selama badai, berpotensi
                    berkontribusi pada kerentanan peralatan.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-footer editable" contenteditable="false">
          Prepared by: Imam Wahyudi – Senior Microwave Technical Support
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Slide 9: Solution 2 -->
      <div class="slide" id="slide9">
        <div class="slide-indicator">
          8 / 12
          <button class="lang-toggle" onclick="toggleLanguage()">
            <i class="fas fa-language"></i> ID
          </button>
          <button class="theme-toggle" onclick="toggleTheme()">
            <i class="fas fa-moon"></i>
          </button>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-header">
          <div class="en-content">
            <h2 class="slide-title editable" contenteditable="false">
              Technical Solution 2: Complete Link Failure
            </h2>
          </div>
          <div class="id-content">
            <h2 class="slide-title editable" contenteditable="false">
              Solusi Teknis 2: Kegagalan Link Total
            </h2>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-content">
          <div class="solution-steps">
            <div class="step en-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-ambulance"></i> Emergency Response
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Activated disaster recovery plan within 30 minutes of incident
                  detection
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Deployed temporary satellite connection to maintain critical
                  services
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Dispatched technical team with spare equipment to both sites
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="step en-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-tools"></i> Hardware Replacement
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Replaced both ODUs with spare units from inventory
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Installed additional surge protection devices at both ends
                </li>
                <li class="editable=" contenteditable="false">
                  Replaced damaged Ethernet switches and verified network
                  connectivity
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Tested all power systems and stabilized voltage regulators
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="step en-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-cogs"></i> System Recommissioning
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Performed complete alignment of antennas using GPS coordinates
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Configured system parameters including frequency, modulation,
                  and capacity
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Conducted end-to-end testing with loopback tests and BER
                  measurements
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Integrated link back into network management system
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="step en-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> Enhanced Protection
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Upgraded lightning protection system with additional grounding
                  rods
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Installed fiber optic isolators between IDUs and network
                  equipment
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Implemented remote power monitoring with automatic shutdown
                  capabilities
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Established quarterly testing schedule for all protection
                  systems
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="step id-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-ambulance"></i> Respons Darurat
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Mengaktifkan rencana pemulihan bencana dalam 30 menit setelah
                  deteksi insiden
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Menyebarkan koneksi satelit sementara untuk mempertahankan
                  layanan kritis
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Mengirim tim teknis dengan peralatan cadangan ke kedua situs
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="step id-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-tools"></i> Penggantian Perangkat Keras
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Mengganti kedua ODU dengan unit cadangan dari inventaris
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Memasang perangkat proteksi surge tambahan di kedua ujung
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Mengganti switch Ethernet yang rusak dan memverifikasi
                  konektivitas jaringan
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Menguji semua sistem daya dan menstabilkan regulator tegangan
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="step id-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-cogs"></i> Pengkomisian Ulang Sistem
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Melakukan alignment antena lengkap menggunakan koordinat GPS
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Mengkonfigurasi parameter sistem termasuk frekuensi, modulasi,
                  dan kapasitas
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Melakukan pengujian end-to-end dengan tes loopback dan
                  pengukuran BER
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Mengintegrasikan link kembali ke sistem manajemen jaringan
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="step id-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> Proteksi yang Ditingkatkan
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Meningkatkan sistem proteksi petir dengan grounding rod
                  tambahan
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Memasang isolator serat optik antara IDU dan peralatan
                  jaringan
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Mengimplementasikan pemantauan daya jarak jauh dengan
                  kemampuan shutdown otomatis
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Membuat jadwal pengujian triwulan untuk semua sistem proteksi
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-footer editable" contenteditable="false">
          Prepared by: Imam Wahyudi – Senior Microwave Technical Support
        </div>
