      <!-- Slide 10: Technical Case 3 -->
      <div class="slide" id="slide10">
        <div class="slide-indicator">
          9 / 12
          <button class="lang-toggle" onclick="toggleLanguage()">
            <i class="fas fa-language"></i> ID
          </button>
          <button class="theme-toggle" onclick="toggleTheme()">
            <i class="fas fa-moon"></i>
          </button>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-header">
          <div class="en-content">
            <h2 class="slide-title editable" contenteditable="false">
              Technical Case 3: Intermittent High BER
            </h2>
          </div>
          <div class="id-content">
            <h2 class="slide-title editable" contenteditable="false">
              Kasus Teknis 3: BER Tinggi Intermittent
            </h2>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-content">
          <div class="case-description">
            <div class="bilingual">
              <div class="column en-content">
                <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Case Description
                </h3>
                <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Incident:</strong> A 15 GHz microwave link serving as
                  a backup connection between two corporate offices experienced
                  intermittent high BER events. The BER would spike from normal
                  levels (&lt;10⁻⁹) to unacceptable levels (&gt;10⁻³) for
                  periods of 5-30 minutes, then return to normal.
                </p>
                <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Impact:</strong> During high BER periods, data
                  transmission would fail, causing application timeouts and
                  retransmissions. The link was operating as backup, so primary
                  services were not affected, but failover testing revealed the
                  issue.
                </p>
                <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Initial Investigation:</strong> Standard diagnostics
                  showed no hardware faults. The issue occurred at various times
                  of day and weather conditions, making it difficult to
                  correlate with environmental factors.
                </p>
                <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Root Cause Analysis
                </h3>
                <ul>
                  <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                    <i class="fas fa-broadcast-tower"></i>
                    <strong>External Interference</strong> – Spectrum analysis
                    revealed intermittent signals on adjacent channels from a
                    newly installed 5G base station 2 km away. The interference
                    occurred during peak usage periods.
                  </li>
                  <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                    <i class="fas fa-cogs"></i>
                    <strong>Adaptive Modulation Issues</strong> – The radio's
                    ACM (Adaptive Coding and Modulation) system was too
                    aggressive, switching to high-order modulation (256-QAM)
                    even when conditions were marginal.
                  </li>
                  <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                    <i class="fas fa-wind"></i>
                    <strong>Atmospheric Ducting</strong> – Unusual weather
                    patterns caused atmospheric ducting, allowing signals from
                    distant sources to interfere with the link.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="column id-content">
                <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Deskripsi Kasus
                </h3>
                <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Insiden:</strong> Link microwave 15 GHz yang berfungsi
                  sebagai koneksi cadangan antara dua kantor perusahaan
                  mengalami peristiwa BER tinggi yang intermiten. BER akan
                  melonjak dari level normal (&lt;10⁻⁹) ke level tidak dapat
                  diterima (&gt;10⁻³) selama periode 5-30 menit, kemudian
                  kembali normal.
                </p>
                <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Dampak:</strong> Selama periode BER tinggi, transmisi
                  data akan gagal, menyebabkan timeout aplikasi dan retransmisi.
                  Link beroperasi sebagai cadangan, jadi layanan utama tidak
                  terpengaruh, tetapi pengujian failover mengungkap masalah.
                </p>
                <p class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <strong>Investigasi Awal:</strong> Diagnostik standar tidak
                  menunjukkan fault perangkat keras. Masalah terjadi pada
                  berbagai waktu sehari dan kondisi cuaca, membuatnya sulit
                  dikorelasikan dengan faktor lingkungan.
                </p>
                <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Analisis Akar Masalah
                </h3>
                <ul>
                  <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                    <i class="fas fa-broadcast-tower"></i>
                    <strong>Interferensi Eksternal</strong> – Analisis spektrum
                    mengungkapkan sinyal intermiten pada kanal yang berdekatan
                    dari stasiun basis 5G yang baru dipasang 2 km jauhnya.
                    Interferensi terjadi selama periode penggunaan puncak.
                  </li>
                  <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                    <i class="fas fa-cogs"></i>
                    <strong>Masalah Modulasi Adaptif</strong> – Sistem ACM
                    (Adaptive Coding and Modulation) radio terlalu agresif,
                    beralih ke modulasi orde tinggi (256-QAM) bahkan ketika
                    kondisi marjinal.
                  </li>
                  <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                    <i class="fas fa-wind"></i>
                    <strong>Ducting Atmosfer</strong> – Pola cuaca tidak biasa
                    menyebabkan ducting atmosfer, memungkinkan sinyal dari
                    sumber jauh mengganggu link.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-footer editable" contenteditable="false">
          Prepared by: Imam Wahyudi – Senior Microwave Technical Support
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Slide 11: Solution 3 -->
      <div class="slide" id="slide11">
        <div class="slide-indicator">
          10 / 12
          <button class="lang-toggle" onclick="toggleLanguage()">
            <i class="fas fa-language"></i> ID
          </button>
          <button class="theme-toggle" onclick="toggleTheme()">
            <i class="fas fa-moon"></i>
          </button>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-header">
          <div class="en-content">
            <h2 class="slide-title editable" contenteditable="false">
              Technical Solution 3: Intermittent High BER
            </h2>
          </div>
          <div class="id-content">
            <h2 class="slide-title editable" contenteditable="false">
              Solusi Teknis 3: BER Tinggi Intermittent
            </h2>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-content">
          <div class="solution-steps">
            <div class="step en-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-chart-bar"></i> Interference Mitigation
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Coordinated with 5G operator to adjust frequency plan and
                  reduce transmit power during critical periods
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Installed band-pass filters to reject out-of-band interference
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Optimized antenna polarization to minimize coupling with
                  interfering signals
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="step en-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-cogs"></i> Radio Configuration
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Modified ACM parameters to be more conservative, maintaining
                  lower modulation during marginal conditions
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Implemented fixed modulation mode during peak interference
                  periods as a temporary measure
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Adjusted power levels to optimize signal-to-interference ratio
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="step en-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-tools"></i> Hardware Optimization
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Replaced standard antennas with high-performance models
                  featuring better side-lobe suppression
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Upgraded transmission lines to low-loss variants
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Installed additional shielding on connectors and cables
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="step en-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i> Monitoring and Maintenance
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Implemented continuous spectrum monitoring with automated
                  alerts for interference detection
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Established regular performance reviews to identify trends and
                  potential issues
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Created procedures for rapid response to interference events
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="step id-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-chart-bar"></i> Mitigasi Interferensi
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Berkoordinasi dengan operator 5G untuk menyesuaikan rencana
                  frekuensi dan mengurangi daya transmisi selama periode kritis
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Memasang filter band-pass untuk menolak interferensi
                  out-of-band
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Mengoptimalkan polarisasi antena untuk meminimalkan coupling
                  dengan sinyal yang mengganggu
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="step id-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-cogs"></i> Konfigurasi Radio
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Memodifikasi parameter ACM untuk lebih konservatif,
                  mempertahankan modulasi lebih rendah selama kondisi marjinal
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Mengimplementasikan mode modulasi tetap selama periode
                  interferensi puncak sebagai langkah sementara
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Menyesuaikan level daya untuk mengoptimalkan
                  signal-to-interference ratio
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="step id-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-tools"></i> Optimasi Perangkat Keras
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Mengganti antena standar dengan model kinerja tinggi yang
                  menampilkan penekanan side-lobe yang lebih baik
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Meningkatkan jalur transmisi ke varian low-loss
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Memasang perisai tambahan pada konektor dan kabel
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="step id-content">
              <h4 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                <i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i> Pemantauan dan Pemeliharaan
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Mengimplementasikan pemantauan spektrum kontinu dengan
                  peringatan otomatis untuk deteksi interferensi
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Membuat ulasan performa reguler untuk mengidentifikasi tren
                  dan masalah potensial
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  Membuat prosedur untuk respons cepat terhadap peristiwa
                  interferensi
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-footer editable" contenteditable="false">
          Prepared by: Imam Wahyudi – Senior Microwave Technical Support
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Slide 12: Best Practices -->
      <div class="slide" id="slide12">
        <div class="slide-indicator">
          11 / 12
          <button class="lang-toggle" onclick="toggleLanguage()">
            <i class="fas fa-language"></i> ID
          </button>
          <button class="theme-toggle" onclick="toggleTheme()">
            <i class="fas fa-moon"></i>
          </button>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-header">
          <div class="en-content">
            <h2 class="slide-title editable" contenteditable="false">
              Best Practices
            </h2>
          </div>
          <div class="id-content">
            <h2 class="slide-title editable" contenteditable="false">
              Praktik Terbaik
            </h2>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-content">
          <div class="bilingual">
            <div class="column en-content">
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Design and Planning
              </h3>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-map"></i>
                  <strong>Comprehensive Path Survey:</strong> Conduct detailed
                  site surveys including path profiling, obstacle analysis, and
                  interference assessment before deployment
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-calculator"></i>
                  <strong>Adequate Fade Margin:</strong> Design links with
                  sufficient fade margin (20-40 dB) to account for atmospheric
                  conditions and equipment aging
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i>
                  <strong>Redundancy Planning:</strong> Implement diverse
                  routing and protection switching for critical links
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-cloud-sun"></i>
                  <strong>Environmental Considerations:</strong> Account for
                  local weather patterns, temperature extremes, and seasonal
                  variations
                </li>
              </ul>
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Installation and Commissioning
              </h3>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-tools"></i>
                  <strong>Quality Installation:</strong> Use certified
                  technicians and follow manufacturer specifications for all
                  hardware
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-crosshairs"></i>
                  <strong>Precise Alignment:</strong> Utilize professional
                  alignment tools and verify with spectrum analyzers
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-bolt"></i>
                  <strong>Proper Grounding:</strong> Implement comprehensive
                  grounding and lightning protection systems
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-clipboard-check"></i>
                  <strong>Thorough Testing:</strong> Conduct comprehensive
                  acceptance testing including BER tests and throughput
                  validation
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="column id-content">
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Desain dan Perencanaan
              </h3>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-map"></i>
                  <strong>Survei Jalur Komprehensif:</strong> Lakukan survei
                  situs terperinci termasuk profiling jalur, analisis rintangan,
                  dan asesmen interferensi sebelum penyebaran
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-calculator"></i>
                  <strong>Fade Margin yang Memadai:</strong> Rancang link dengan
                  fade margin yang cukup (20-40 dB) untuk memperhitungkan
                  kondisi atmosfer dan penuaan peralatan
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i>
                  <strong>Perencanaan Redundansi:</strong> Implementasikan
                  routing yang beragam dan proteksi switching untuk link kritis
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-cloud-sun"></i>
                  <strong>Pertimbangan Lingkungan:</strong> Perhitungkan pola
                  cuaca lokal, suhu ekstrem, dan variasi musiman
                </li>
              </ul>
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Instalasi dan Komisioning
              </h3>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-tools"></i>
                  <strong>Instalasi Berkualitas:</strong> Gunakan teknisi
                  bersertifikat dan ikuti spesifikasi produsen untuk semua
                  perangkat keras
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-crosshairs"></i>
                  <strong>Alignment Presisi:</strong> Gunakan alat alignment
                  profesional dan verifikasi dengan spectrum analyzer
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-bolt"></i>
                  <strong>Grounding yang Tepat:</strong> Implementasikan sistem
                  grounding dan proteksi petir yang komprehensif
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-clipboard-check"></i>
                  <strong>Pengujian Thorough:</strong> Lakukan pengujian
                  penerimaan komprehensif termasuk tes BER dan validasi
                  throughput
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bilingual">
            <div class="column en-content">
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Operations and Maintenance
              </h3>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i>
                  <strong>Continuous Monitoring:</strong> Implement 24/7
                  monitoring with automated alerts for performance degradation
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-calendar-check"></i>
                  <strong>Preventive Maintenance:</strong> Establish regular
                  inspection schedules and perform proactive maintenance
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-database"></i>
                  <strong>Performance Analysis:</strong> Regularly review
                  performance metrics and trends to identify potential issues
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-users"></i>
                  <strong>Staff Training:</strong> Ensure technical staff are
                  properly trained on equipment and troubleshooting procedures
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="column id-content">
              <h3 class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                Operasi dan Pemeliharaan
              </h3>
              <ul>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i>
                  <strong>Pemantauan Kontinu:</strong> Implementasikan
                  pemantauan 24/7 dengan peringatan otomatis untuk degradasi
                  performa
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-calendar-check"></i>
                  <strong>Pemeliharaan Preventif:</strong> Buat jadwal inspeksi
                  reguler dan lakukan pemeliharaan proaktif
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-database"></i>
                  <strong>Analisis Performa:</strong> Tinjau secara teratur
                  metrik performa dan tren untuk mengidentifikasi masalah
                  potensial
                </li>
                <li class="editable" contenteditable="false">
                  <i class="fas fa-users"></i>
                  <strong>Pelatihan Staf:</strong> Pastikan staf teknis dilatih
                  dengan benar pada peralatan dan prosedur pemecahan masalah
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-footer editable" contenteditable="false">
          Prepared by: Imam Wahyudi – Senior Microwave Technical Support
        </div>
